This directory contains collections of materials.  Materials are
defined as the spectral and surface properties of 3D objects.
This may contain references to texture information.

However, texture and image maps should NOT be installed here;
use /usr/data/images/*.


File format is denoted by the suffix.
For example, files with `.iv' are IRIS Inventor format.


IRIS Inventor Notes:
    . use `ivcat' to convert binary Inventor files to ascii (e.g. ivcat cube.iv)
    . use `ivinfo' to get a summary of an Inventor file contents
